-- Hungarian govt says will continue talks with IMF/EU
-- 
-- Sat Jul 17, 2010 4:44pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/07/17/us-hungary-imf-govt-idUSTRE66G1MF20100717

 

 BUDAPEST  (Reuters) - Hungary's government will continue talks with the country's international lenders and will implement structural reforms in key areas, Economy Minister Gyorgy Matolcsy said in a statement on Saturday. 

 "The government will of course continue talks with international organizations including the IMF and the EU," Matolcsy said in a statement published by national news agency MTI. (Reporting by Krisztina Than)